result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
9:16 AM Defendant Dustin J Smith in court.  Prosecuting attorney Melissa J. Zilavy in court for the State of Wisconsin. Victim rights have been complied with by the Waukesha County District Attorneys Office. 

Defendant confirms he is unrepresented by counsel. Court advises Defendant of possible maximum penalties. Court advises of right to an attorney. Court advises the Defendant of possibility of Public Defender counsel be appointed. 

Court will set case over for another date, but directs the Defendant to go to the PD's office for evaluation, and advises of petition for court appointed counsel.
Hearing scheduled for November 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Motion Order to Seal Victim Identification Key, Signed by Judge Carter on 09/19/2022

Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing. Defendant to have no contact with victims A & B listed in the Criminal Complaint/Victim Identification Key.  Defendant is not to share, reproduce or distribute any personal and/or identifying information about the crime victim(s), except to their attorney. Defendant allowed one trip to the residence accompanied by a peace/police officer to obtain personal items.

1:13 PM District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Jack Rieder. Defendant Dustin J Smith in court, in custody. 

Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading of complaint. 
Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties. 
Court advises of right to an attorney.
NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED BY COURT.
Hearing scheduled for October 10, 2022 at 09:00 am.
Waukesha County Public Safety Assessment Report filed by Wisconsin Community Services.
Victim/Witness Identification Key filed, under seal, by the District Attorney's office.
